-- Chilean Stocks: CFR, Empresas La Polar, Lan Airlines, Salfacorp
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-01-13T21:00:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/chilean-stocks-cfr-pharmaceuticals-lan-airlines-salfacorp.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa (IPSA)  index fell 0.2 percent to 4,205.05. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index retreated 0.5 percent to 2,344.43.  CFR Pharmaceuticals SA (CFR)  (CFR CC) rose 0.7 percent to 121.98
pesos, its second day of gains. The Chilean drug developer
completed the acquisition of Vietnam’s Domesco Medical Import
Export Joint Stock Corp for $14.3 million and will pay dividends
of $16.6 million, according to statements posted yesterday on
the website of Chile’s securities regulator.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)  (LAPOLAR CC) fell 3.2 percent to 258
pesos. The Chilean department-store operator under  bankruptcy
protection  may have to increase loan-loss provisions by 17
billion pesos ($34 million) and may also see a 14 billion-peso
drop in consumer loan repayments, after a court ordered the
company to suspend restructuring of client debt.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   advanced 0.3 percent to 12,372
pesos, the highest price in three weeks.  Latin America ’s largest
airline by market value said savings from the takeover of
 Brazil ’s  Tam SA (TAMM4)  will reach between $600 million and $700
million, compared to a previous estimate of $400 million.  Salfacorp SA (SALFACOR)   rose 1 percent to 1,294 pesos,
the biggest advance in three weeks. Chile’s largest construction
company expects revenue to grow as much as 15 percent in 2012,
according to a presentation posted on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
